16
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,660
Under what circumstances would someone

17
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:38,160
pour a second cup of tea

18
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,880
when the first one still has tea in it?

19
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,160
My guess is

20
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:51,400
Mu Weijie went back to his room to take medicine

21
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,120
because he felt unwell.

22
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,960
But when he picked up the teacup,

23
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:12,400
he suddenly remembered that tea would affect the medicine's efficacy.

24
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,360
So he put down the cup

25
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,960
and got up to pour another glass of water.

26
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:40,960
So I presume he needed to take medicine that day,

27
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:43,760
which is why he used two cups.

28
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:45,680
And the medicine he took

29
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,360
might be the key to solving the case.

30
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,120
Stop.

31
00:03:58,720 --> 00:03:59,960
Lin Rongrong said

32
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:03,200
